et with school and division department heads to discuss potential projects and to review the format for submitting facility budget requests fbrs to those new to the campus and new to the process to get started just login with your netid and password any suggestions for improvement are welcome for future revisions of the web site intro traditionally there have been many more annual capital budget requests than could be supported from available university funds as a result only the top priority requests from each school and division are investigated and priced the budget committee closely scrutinizes the highest priority items therefore actively screen all potential projects and forward only the top candidates in priority order the expectation that a  funding contribution be made for each project from each school and division will continue this year please designate the fundorg for local contributions for the funding source as requested on the request template the capital budget list is limited to projects that exceed  fy  capital budget planning schedule date activity september   kickoff letter to campus announcing start of fy  capital budget process september   september   project development meetings scheduled with each school and division as necessary to discuss projects likely to be requested identify major planning issues september   deadline for all fbrs october   october   compilation of list and followup questions to requestors october   december   facilities engineering  planning project management and engineering staff work with designated client representatives to define scopes of work and establish cost estimates note deadline for all requests is december   week of october   first review of capital project requests provost vpa vpf fep week of december   fep distributes documentation on cost estimates for academic requests and deans meet individually with provost to discuss requests site visits for proposed requests scheduled with the provost if necessary vice president for administration is briefed on all nonacademic requests december  as necessary update project scope and pricing changes from provost review january  review committee indepth review of capital project requests february  recommended list finalized and shared with schools and divisions march  presentation of the fy  annual capital budget to the building and grounds committee the bg recommends approval of the annual capital budget by the board of trustees at the march board meeting marchmay  communicate results of board action format for requests please submit requests using the annual capital budget website the deadline to submit requests is friday september   request template the request template has been formatted to summarize important information on potential projects potential projects are evaluated on such factors as cost benefit alternative solutions and the consequences of not doing the project tool tips have been included in the request template to assist in identifying this additional information estimates facilities engineering and planning fep staff will work with designated contacts to confirm requirements and to develop cost estimates meetings ana ramirez and pat dwyer will meet with school and division department heads to discuss potential projects and to answer any questions about the fbr submittal process rene salinas extension  lrsriceedu will be calling to arrange these meetings to take place sometime during the month of september if it is not necessary to meet please contact ana ramirez annual capital budget review process facilities engineering and planning main ms houston texas        mailing address po box  houston texas   rice university rice homeweb servicesuniversity calendarrice azmapsdirectionsfeedback private equity funds – starling family office global vision private equity funds bain capital bain capital is one of the world’s leading private equity investment firms with more than  investment professionals and over  billio